MacAndrews and Forbes Group Inc said itbegan an 18.50-dlr-a-share cash offer for all common stock ofRevlon Group Inc it does not already own.    The offer, which is being made by a wholly ownedsubsidiary, Revmac Acquisition Corp, is subject to financingand at least 28.5 mln shares being tendered, the company said.    MacAndrews and Forbes, wholly owned by Ronald Perelman,chairman of Revlon Group, held about 31.8 pct of the votingpower of Revlon as of March 27, a spokesman said. The stakeincludes about 15.1 pct of Revlon common and 95 pct of itsseries A preferred stock, he said. More&#3;